40|$|In any {{application}} {{involving the}} production, storage {{or use of}} hydrogen, sensors are important devices for alerting {{to the presence of}} leaked hydrogen. Hydrogen sensors should be accurate, sensitive, and specific, as well as resistant to long term drift and varying environmental conditions. Furthermore, as an integral element in a <b>safety</b> system, <b>sensor</b> performance should not be compromised by operational parameters. For example, <b>safety</b> <b>sensors</b> may be required to operate at reduced oxygen levels relative to air. In this work we evaluate and compare a number of sensor technologies in terms of their ability to detect hydrogen under conditions of varying oxygen concentration. JRC. F. 2 -Cleaner energ...|$|R
40|$|The EU-funded project VALERI {{aimed to}} {{validate}} the use of mobile manipulators for aerospace production. This paper focuses on the development and application of tactile sensors for safeguarding the mobile platform and to allow for in-tuitive haptic interaction when operating {{in close proximity to}} human co-workers. The sensor design and experimental results when used as a <b>safety</b> <b>sensor</b> and for haptic user interaction will be described in this article...|$|E
